    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - Meritor Medium Duty Front Drive Steer Axle - Assembly and Installation - Assemble
        Slack Adjuster
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>Assemble Slack Adjuster</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the air brake chamber and bracket (Figure 52). Tighten the bracket mounting
                capscrews to the correct torque specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s02012_59.xml" xrefid="x0201201">Fastener Torque Chart</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201252" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201252.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 52. Install Air Brake Chamber and Bracket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the inner washer on the camshaft, then install the slack adjuster onto the camshaft
                (Figure 53).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201253" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201253.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 53. Install Slack Adjuster</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install slack adjuster washers at the adjuster end of the camshaft (Figure 54). Use as many
                washers as required to keep slack end play at 0.060-inch (1.5 mm) maximum.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201254" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201254.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 54. Install Slack Adjuster Washers</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the slack adjuster retaining ring at the adjuster end of the camshaft (Figure 55).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201255" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201255.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 55. Install Slack Adjuster Retaining Ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the pin and retainer that engages the push rod yoke and the slack adjuster plunger
                rod (Figure 56).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201256" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201256.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 56. Install Pin and Retainer</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Adjust slack adjuster position to obtain the following BSAP dimension from the back of the
                brake air chamber to the center of the clevis pin:
            </para>
        </step1>
        <table id="t0201203">
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col1"/>
                <colspec colname="col2"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>SL (Slack Adjuster Length)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>BSAP (Brake Slack Adjuster Position)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="col1">
                            <para>5.5 inches (139.7 mm)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="col2">
                            <para>7.4 inches (188 mm)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tighten the nut on the push rod to the clevis pin to the proper torque shown in the
                <hotlnk document="s02012_59.xml" xrefid="x0201201">Fastener Torque Chart</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the air lines to the brake chambers.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the brake drum (Figure 57).</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the axle lubricant level and fill if required. Refer to Meritor Maintenance Manual 1,
                Lubrication, for lubricant specifications.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201257" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201257.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 57. Install Brake Drum</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
